---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How PepCodex collects, uses, and protects your personal information. Our commitment to your privacy."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="font-serif mt-4 text-4xl tracking-tight" style="color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500;">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xl" style="color: var(--ink-muted);">
        How we handle your data with respect and transparency.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--ink-dim);">Last updated: June 2026</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <!-- Introduction -->
      <section id="introduction">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          PepCodex ("we," "our," or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your
          personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard
          your information when you visit pepcodex.com ("the Website") or use the PepTracker
          mobile app ("PepTracker" or "the App").
        </p>
        <p>
          Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this
          Privacy Policy, please do not access the Website or use the App.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Information We Collect -->
      <section id="information-collected" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>Information Automatically Collected</h3>
        <p>
          When you visit the Website, we may automatically collect certain information about your
          device and your visit, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Device Information:</strong> Browser type, operating system, device type,
            screen resolution
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, time spent on pages, click patterns,
            referring website, exit pages
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Location Data:</strong> General geographic location based on IP address
            (country/region level only)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, internet service provider
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
        <p>
          We may collect information that you voluntarily provide to us, such as:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Newsletter Subscription:</strong> Email address when you subscribe to our newsletter
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact Forms:</strong> Name, email address, and message content when you
            contact us
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Feedback:</strong> Any information you provide when submitting corrections
            or suggestions
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>PepTracker Mobile App Data</h3>
        <p>
          PepTracker is designed as a local-first mobile app. Protocols, doses, vials, weight
          entries, body-fat entries, check-ins, side effects, injection sites, bloodwork values,
          reminders, profile preferences, and unit settings are stored on your device with local
          app storage and SQLite. PepTracker does not require an account for V1 tracking features
          and does not sync this tracking data to a PepTracker backend.
        </p>
        <p>
          Health-tracking data from the App does not leave your device unless you choose to export
          or share it through your operating system's share sheet, connect a third-party service
          described below, or submit information to us separately through a support channel.
        </p>

        <h3>Health Connect on Android</h3>
        <p>
          If you connect Health Connect on Android, PepTracker requests read access only for weight
          and body-fat records. Authorized records are imported into the App's local database so
          they can appear beside your protocol logs and trends. PepTracker does not write data back
          to Health Connect and does not request broader Health Connect categories in V1.
        </p>

        <h3>Purchases and Subscriptions</h3>
        <p>
          Premium subscriptions are processed by Apple, Google, and RevenueCat. RevenueCat manages
          anonymous purchase and entitlement state for the App. PepTracker V1 does not collect a
          name, email address, password, or account login for core tracking features.
        </p>

        <h3>Crash and Error Reports</h3>
        <p>
          Production builds of the App may send crash and error diagnostics to Sentry when crash
          reporting is configured. The App is designed to scrub events before upload by removing
          user and request context, dropping event extras and log parameters, redacting health-like
          key/value text from messages, exception values, and stack context, stripping breadcrumb
          data, and disabling performance tracing and session replay.
        </p>

        <h3>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>
        <p>
          We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to collect information about your
          browsing activities. For detailed information about the cookies we use, please see our
          <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- How We Use Your Information -->
      <section id="how-we-use" class="mt-12">
        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Operate, maintain, and improve the Website</li>
          <li>Send you newsletters if you have subscribed (you can unsubscribe at any time)</li>
          <li>Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support</li>
          <li>Analyze usage patterns to improve user experience</li>
          <li>Monitor and analyze trends, usage, and activities</li>
          <li>Detect, prevent, and address technical issues</li>
          <li>Process App subscription status and Premium entitlement state</li>
          <li>Import Health Connect data only when you grant permission</li>
          <li>Schedule App reminders locally on your device</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)</h3>
        <p>
          If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), our legal basis for collecting
          and using your personal information depends on the data concerned and the context in
          which we collect it:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Consent:</strong> Where you have given us consent (e.g., newsletter subscription,
            non-essential cookies)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legitimate Interests:</strong> Where processing is necessary for our legitimate
            interests (e.g., website analytics, security) and not overridden by your rights
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> Where we need to comply with a legal obligation
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Analytics -->
      <section id="analytics" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          We use Google Analytics 4 to help us understand how visitors use the Website. Google
          Analytics collects information such as:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>How often users visit the Website</li>
          <li>What pages they visit</li>
          <li>How long they stay on each page</li>
          <li>What other sites they visited before coming to our Website</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Google Analytics uses cookies and similar technologies. The information generated is
          transmitted to and stored by Google on servers in the United States. Google may use
          this information to evaluate your use of the Website, compile reports on website
          activity, and provide other services related to website activity and internet usage.
        </p>
        <p>
          For more information about Google Analytics and privacy, visit:
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Google Privacy Policy
          </a>
        </p>
        <p>
          You can opt-out of Google Analytics by installing the
          <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on
          </a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Data Sharing -->
      <section id="data-sharing" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share
          your information in the following circumstances:
        </p>

        <h3>Service Providers</h3>
        <p>
          We may share your information with third-party service providers who perform services
          on our behalf, such as:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Website hosting providers</li>
          <li>Email service providers (for newsletter delivery)</li>
          <li>Analytics providers</li>
          <li>Payment and subscription entitlement providers</li>
          <li>Crash and error reporting providers</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These service providers are contractually obligated to use your information only for
          the purposes of providing services to us and to maintain appropriate security measures.
        </p>

        <h3>Legal Requirements</h3>
        <p>
          We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid
          requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or government agency).
        </p>

        <h3>Business Transfers</h3>
        <p>
          If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may
          be transferred as part of that transaction. We will provide notice before your
          information becomes subject to a different privacy policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Data Retention -->
      <section id="data-retention" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the
          purposes for which it was collected, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics Data:</strong> Retained for 14 months by Google Analytics (default setting)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Newsletter Subscriptions:</strong> Until you unsubscribe or request deletion
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact Form Submissions:</strong> Retained for up to 2 years or until the
            inquiry is resolved
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>PepTracker App Data:</strong> Stored locally on your device until you delete it,
            uninstall the App, or clear local app data. We cannot recover local App data that you
            delete or lose.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- App Data Controls -->
      <section id="app-data-controls" class="mt-12">
        <h2>PepTracker App Data Controls</h2>
        <p>
          PepTracker includes a Clear All Data / Delete My Data control that removes local SQLite
          records, app preference keys, and scheduled local notifications from your device. Because
          V1 is local-first and has no PepTracker account backend, deleted local App data cannot be
          recovered by PepTracker.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can revoke Health Connect access in the App's data-source controls or through Android
          Health Connect settings. Revoking access stops future imports.
        </p>
        <p>
          Exports are user-initiated. When you export Text, JSON, or HTML data, the App assembles
          the selected payload locally and hands it to the operating system share sheet. The
          destination app or service you choose controls its own privacy practices.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Your Rights -->
      <section id="your-rights" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal
          information:
        </p>

        <h3>For All Users</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Unsubscribe:</strong> You can unsubscribe from our newsletter at any time
            by clicking the unsubscribe link in any email
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cookie Preferences:</strong> You can manage your cookie preferences through
            your browser settings or our cookie consent tool
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>For EEA/UK Residents (GDPR)</h3>
        <p>Under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data ("right to be forgotten")</li>
          <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> Request restriction of processing</li>
          <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Request transfer of your data to another service</li>
          <li><strong>Objection:</strong> Object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
          <li><strong>Withdraw Consent:</strong> Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>For California Residents (CCPA)</h3>
        <p>Under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Know what personal information is collected</li>
          <li>Know whether your personal information is sold or disclosed</li>
          <li>Say no to the sale of personal information (we do not sell your data)</li>
          <li>Access your personal information</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your personal information</li>
          <li>Not be discriminated against for exercising your rights</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
          <a href="mailto:privacy@pepcodex.com">privacy@pepcodex.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Data Security -->
      <section id="security" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect
          your personal information, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>HTTPS encryption for all data transmission</li>
          <li>Regular security assessments</li>
          <li>Access controls and authentication</li>
          <li>Secure hosting infrastructure</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          However, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage
          is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your
          personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- International Transfers -->
      <section id="international-transfers" class="mt-12">
        <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your
          country of residence, including the United States. These countries may have data
          protection laws that are different from the laws of your country.
        </p>
        <p>
          When we transfer data internationally, we take appropriate safeguards to ensure that
          your personal information remains protected in accordance with this Privacy Policy
          and applicable law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Children's Privacy -->
      <section id="children" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The Website and App are not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly
          collect personal information from children under 18. If you are a parent or guardian
          and believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact
          us so that we can delete the information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Third-Party Links -->
      <section id="third-party-links" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          The Website and App may contain links to third-party websites, including scientific journals,
          research databases, regulatory agencies, and App Store or Google Play subscription
          management surfaces. We are not responsible for the privacy
          practices of these third-party websites. We encourage you to review the privacy
          policies of any website you visit.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Changes to Policy -->
      <section id="changes" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes
          by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
        </p>
        <p>
          We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Your
          continued use of the Website after any modifications indicates your acceptance of
          the updated Privacy Policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <section id="contact" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices,
          please contact us:
        </p>
        <p>
          Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@pepcodex.com">privacy@pepcodex.com</a>
        </p>
        <p>
          For GDPR-related inquiries, you may also contact our Data Protection contact at the
          same email address.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Related Pages -->
      <section id="related" class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-[color:var(--border-c)]">
        <h2>Related Legal Pages</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a></li>
          <li><a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a></li>
          <li><a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="/fda-notice">FDA Notice</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
